1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:32,000
(Watch on www.kisskh.xyz Support Admin)

2
00:00:45,254 --> 00:00:48,966
PERFECT CROWN

3
00:00:59,851 --> 00:01:00,978
THIS IS A WORK OF FICTION

4
00:01:01,061 --> 00:01:02,980
CHILD ACTORS AND ANIMALS
WERE FILMED SAFELY

5
00:01:07,150 --> 00:01:08,485
64TH ARCHERY EXHIBITION MATCH

6
00:01:08,569 --> 00:01:10,821
Hyeonmu House,
Black Tortoise of the North!

7
00:01:12,447 --> 00:01:14,950
Cheongnyong House,
Azure Dragon of the East!

8
00:01:21,331 --> 00:01:23,333
Jujak House, Vermilion Bird of the South!

9
00:01:30,882 --> 00:01:32,968
Baekho House, White Tiger of the West!

10
00:01:33,885 --> 00:01:35,220
That brat is Jujak's rep?

11
00:01:36,388 --> 00:01:38,098
She's pretty good. I saw her practice.

12
00:01:38,807 --> 00:01:41,560
I got this key from Ryu Minseok,
Cheongnyong House, ninth grade.

13
00:01:42,603 --> 00:01:44,271
She is one vicious brat.

14
00:01:44,354 --> 00:01:47,107
Just last month,
she couldn't even break a seven.

15
00:01:47,899 --> 00:01:49,901
Why are you always so hostile toward her?

16
00:01:49,985 --> 00:01:51,320
Do you like her?

17
00:01:51,945 --> 00:01:54,323
A lowly creature like her?

18
00:01:55,407 --> 00:01:57,034
-Are you insane?
-Ryu Minseok.

19
00:01:57,117 --> 00:01:58,410
Yes?

20
00:01:59,036 --> 00:02:00,203
Watch your mouth.

21
00:02:01,121 --> 00:02:03,040
-Pardon?
-Your vulgarity…

22
00:02:04,833 --> 00:02:06,418
offends my eyes and ears.

23
00:02:10,255 --> 00:02:11,256
Understood.

24
00:02:18,930 --> 00:02:21,516
Let's go, Cheongnyong House!

25
00:02:23,435 --> 00:02:25,228
Good luck!

26
00:02:35,739 --> 00:02:37,491
Ten points!

27
00:02:43,163 --> 00:02:44,581
Nine points!

28
00:02:49,795 --> 00:02:50,837
My goodness.

29
00:02:50,921 --> 00:02:53,590
The students' enthusiasm
is truly remarkable, isn't it?

30
00:02:54,174 --> 00:02:57,260
News of Your Majesty's attendance
really fired them up.

31
00:02:57,928 --> 00:02:59,137
Word has reached me

32
00:02:59,805 --> 00:03:01,723
that the archery range was open
around the clock.

33
00:03:01,807 --> 00:03:03,266
Yes, Your Majesty.

34
00:03:03,850 --> 00:03:06,687
It was a personal request
from Grand Prince I-AN.

35
00:03:19,449 --> 00:03:21,993
Cheongnyong House, you're so cool!

36
00:03:22,077 --> 00:03:24,287
-Go, Cheongnyong House!
-Cheongnyong!

37
00:03:24,371 --> 00:03:27,999
-Cheongnyong of the East!
-Cheongnyong of the East!

38
00:03:45,517 --> 00:03:47,018
Nine points!

39
00:04:00,198 --> 00:04:01,199
Come on…

40
00:04:05,662 --> 00:04:07,247
Ten points!

41
00:04:19,176 --> 00:04:21,178
It's okay. We still have one more round.

42
00:04:22,137 --> 00:04:23,472
We can turn it around then.

43
00:04:35,066 --> 00:04:36,985
HYEONMU, CHEONGNYONG,
JUJAK, BAEKHO

44
00:04:37,819 --> 00:04:40,530
It appears victory belongs to
House Cheongnyong this year.

45
00:04:41,239 --> 00:04:42,532
I am not so sure.

46
00:04:42,616 --> 00:04:43,909
It is not over

47
00:04:44,951 --> 00:04:46,286
until it is truly over.

48
00:04:48,872 --> 00:04:50,707
Last round!

49
00:04:55,420 --> 00:04:57,005
You got this!

50
00:04:57,088 --> 00:04:59,508
-Go, Cheongnyong!
-Go, Jujak!

51
00:04:59,591 --> 00:05:00,759
You got this, Jujak!

52
00:05:34,459 --> 00:05:35,919
Nine points!

53
00:05:36,002 --> 00:05:37,838
110 POINTS

54
00:06:05,490 --> 00:06:07,284
EPISODE 2

55
00:06:10,203 --> 00:06:11,371
Let's…

56
00:06:12,581 --> 00:06:13,582
get married.

57
00:06:46,656 --> 00:06:47,866
What are the terms?

58
00:06:48,783 --> 00:06:49,951
You don't seem surprised.

59
00:06:51,328 --> 00:06:52,329
Why should I be?

60
00:06:52,412 --> 00:06:55,081
-There must've been plenty before me.
-There have.

61
00:06:55,165 --> 00:06:58,501
Just in the past two days,
I've received dozens of match proposals.

62
00:07:05,425 --> 00:07:06,718
Damn it.

63
00:07:11,014 --> 00:07:12,098
So…

64
00:07:13,933 --> 00:07:15,060
state your terms.

65
00:07:19,439 --> 00:07:21,691
I shall personally assess them.

66
00:07:31,826 --> 00:07:32,911
I have a lot of money.

67
00:07:43,588 --> 00:07:46,007
I was expecting something
a little more creative.

68
00:07:46,091 --> 00:07:48,009
No point in wasting creativity.

69
00:07:48,093 --> 00:07:50,136
Arranged marriages are all the same.

70
00:07:51,763 --> 00:07:52,764
After all,

71
00:07:54,557 --> 00:07:56,726
familiarity makes everything feel better,

72
00:07:57,310 --> 00:07:59,771
from the food you eat,
to the path you take,

73
00:08:00,522 --> 00:08:01,815
even the clothes you wear.

74
00:08:03,024 --> 00:08:04,943
That's why you reach for them.

75
00:08:11,449 --> 00:08:12,450
So?

76
00:08:13,159 --> 00:08:14,619
An assessment of the familiarity.

77
00:08:15,412 --> 00:08:17,872
My pedigree is impressive,
and my acumen sharper still.

78
00:08:18,373 --> 00:08:19,874
I have an older brother,

79
00:08:20,583 --> 00:08:21,835
but you don't need to worry.

80
00:08:21,918 --> 00:08:25,004
He's too dumb to cause any trouble.

81
00:08:28,091 --> 00:08:30,468
I know you don't like it
when in-laws overstep.

82
00:08:32,220 --> 00:08:33,221
What else?

83
00:08:41,146 --> 00:08:42,272
I've got thick skin.

84
00:08:43,565 --> 00:08:46,609
A successful woman and the bastard heir
to a conglomerate empire.

85
00:08:47,902 --> 00:08:50,697
Do you have any idea
how much criticism I face every day?

86
00:08:50,780 --> 00:08:54,117
Your Royal Highness
would never know in a million years.

87
00:08:54,200 --> 00:08:55,577
It's better that way.

88
00:08:56,828 --> 00:08:59,080
And I will make sure you never find out.

89
00:09:00,290 --> 00:09:01,374
So just use me

90
00:09:02,375 --> 00:09:03,626
as your human shield.

91
00:09:06,337 --> 00:09:08,423
Pew…

92
00:09:13,595 --> 00:09:16,389
We're getting divorced
once the contract is over anyway.

93
00:09:17,348 --> 00:09:18,725
And even then,

94
00:09:20,143 --> 00:09:21,144
I'll take the hit.

95
00:09:27,484 --> 00:09:28,610
Anything else?

96
00:09:32,864 --> 00:09:33,865
Beauty?

97
00:09:35,867 --> 00:09:36,868
What else?

98
00:09:37,786 --> 00:09:40,080
-You need more?
-Yeah. What else?

99
00:09:50,381 --> 00:09:51,549
Areum?

100
00:09:53,009 --> 00:09:55,136
-Aide Choi.
-What are you doing here?

101
00:09:55,762 --> 00:09:58,598
Well, it's time for his herbal tonic.

102
00:09:59,974 --> 00:10:01,017
Such perfect timing.

103
00:10:01,101 --> 00:10:03,019
I can bring it to him. Give it to me.

104
00:10:03,728 --> 00:10:04,896
Ah…

105
00:10:06,940 --> 00:10:08,650
Your Royal Highness, it is Hyeon.

106
00:10:21,913 --> 00:10:23,456
I-I have your tonic--

107
00:10:23,540 --> 00:10:25,208
-Leave it there and go.
-Yes, sir.

108
00:10:51,192 --> 00:10:52,569
Your Majesty.

109
00:10:52,652 --> 00:10:55,196
Jaegyeong of the Kim Family has arrived.

110
00:10:58,700 --> 00:10:59,701
Show her in.

111
00:11:20,680 --> 00:11:24,350
PERFECT CROWN

112
00:11:24,434 --> 00:11:26,144
CASTLE BEAUTY

113
00:11:26,769 --> 00:11:28,521
-Has Ms. Seong come in yet?
-What?

114
00:11:28,605 --> 00:11:29,772
Yes, she just came in.

115
00:11:40,408 --> 00:11:43,036
What is it? Why are you smiling?

116
00:11:43,995 --> 00:11:45,747
You don't even like me smiling now?

117
00:11:46,456 --> 00:11:48,458
You shouldn't be smiling right now.

118
00:11:48,541 --> 00:11:51,044
Have you lost your mind?
Or are you being punished?

119
00:11:53,630 --> 00:11:56,007
Is he going to force you to drink poison?

120
00:11:57,383 --> 00:11:58,593
Don't be ridiculous.

121
00:11:58,676 --> 00:12:00,094
This isn't the Joseon Dynasty.

122
00:12:00,595 --> 00:12:01,888
Ah…

123
00:12:01,971 --> 00:12:02,972
Exactly.

124
00:12:03,556 --> 00:12:05,892
So what happened? Update me already.

125
00:12:09,187 --> 00:12:10,188
I was rejected.

126
00:12:11,356 --> 00:12:12,398
What?

127
00:12:14,817 --> 00:12:15,944
I said I was rejected.

128
00:12:16,986 --> 00:12:18,029
I decline.

129
00:12:19,489 --> 00:12:21,449
-May I ask why?
-Because there is…

130
00:12:22,784 --> 00:12:26,162
…something I value more
than wealth, ability, and beauty.

131
00:12:26,246 --> 00:12:27,622
And what might that be?

132
00:12:27,705 --> 00:12:28,706
If I tell you,

133
00:12:30,458 --> 00:12:31,542
can you give it to me?

134
00:12:33,711 --> 00:12:34,879
You think I can't?

135
00:12:38,258 --> 00:12:40,510
So? What did he say he needs?

136
00:12:42,553 --> 00:12:43,680
Love.

137
00:12:44,597 --> 00:12:45,598
Huh?

138
00:12:45,682 --> 00:12:47,267
He wishes to marry for love.

139
00:12:49,435 --> 00:12:51,771
It's been his lifelong dream, apparently.

140
00:12:54,607 --> 00:12:56,693
He's more of a romantic than you'd think.

141
00:12:57,360 --> 00:12:59,612
-Romantic, my foot.
-You scared me.

142
00:12:59,696 --> 00:13:01,489
He's clearly just screwing with me.

143
00:13:02,615 --> 00:13:04,367
So you screwed her over.

144
00:13:05,201 --> 00:13:07,203
I thought you two went to the same school.

145
00:13:07,745 --> 00:13:11,040
You could've just said no
and politely declined her offer.

146
00:13:11,124 --> 00:13:12,333
You should've been nicer.

147
00:13:12,417 --> 00:13:13,543
You can be so mean.

148
00:13:17,213 --> 00:13:19,215
I'll look for another candidate.

149
00:13:19,841 --> 00:13:20,842
Why?

150
00:13:22,093 --> 00:13:23,928
Since you were rejected.

151
00:13:24,012 --> 00:13:25,305
So?

152
00:13:25,388 --> 00:13:28,182
What? Are you going to try again?

153
00:13:28,266 --> 00:13:29,392
Yeah.

154
00:13:29,892 --> 00:13:31,936
Why? You weren't even sincere about it.

155
00:13:32,020 --> 00:13:34,355
Oh, please. I couldn't be more sincere.

156
00:13:34,439 --> 00:13:35,523
As if.

157
00:13:35,606 --> 00:13:37,108
What kind of "sincere" person

158
00:13:37,191 --> 00:13:40,028
would say, "I've got money, power,
a deadbeat brother,

159
00:13:40,111 --> 00:13:42,530
and I'll even sign the divorce papers"?

160
00:13:42,613 --> 00:13:44,282
Not a shred of modesty to be found.

161
00:13:44,782 --> 00:13:45,783
Ms. Do.

162
00:13:46,743 --> 00:13:51,664
Prince I-AN is already surrounded
by a horde armed with calculated modesty.

163
00:13:51,748 --> 00:13:54,751
What do you think it'll take
to win against them?

164
00:13:56,461 --> 00:13:59,130
You need a strategy to set yourself apart.

165
00:14:02,550 --> 00:14:05,970
So are you saying
you intentionally pulled that crazy stunt?

166
00:14:06,054 --> 00:14:09,724
I'm sure he's fond of eccentrics like me.

167
00:14:09,807 --> 00:14:11,851
Birds of a feather flock together.

168
00:14:13,186 --> 00:14:17,065
He showed up to His Majesty's
Royal Birthday Banquet in a cheollik.

169
00:14:17,148 --> 00:14:18,983
That's not "normal," is it?

170
00:14:20,401 --> 00:14:23,696
Were you not set
on Jaegyeong of the Kim Family?

171
00:14:23,780 --> 00:14:24,906
PROSPECTIVE CONSORT

172
00:14:24,989 --> 00:14:26,532
I do not intend to play matchmaker.

173
00:14:28,785 --> 00:14:30,369
I would rather remain a spectator.

174
00:14:33,456 --> 00:14:38,086
The more people interfere,
the greater the conflict grows.

175
00:14:38,669 --> 00:14:39,670
In the end,

176
00:14:40,838 --> 00:14:43,216
the one who staged it
will emerge the winner.

177
00:14:43,299 --> 00:14:44,634
Does that mean…

178
00:14:49,305 --> 00:14:50,973
I must meet this maiden.

179
00:15:07,448 --> 00:15:09,617
You said to prepare the new proposal
by next week--

180
00:15:09,700 --> 00:15:11,410
-Listen…
-I'll have it by this evening.

181
00:15:11,994 --> 00:15:13,246
Mm-mmm.

182
00:15:13,996 --> 00:15:16,415
You can give that to me next week.

183
00:15:16,499 --> 00:15:17,500
Pardon?

184
00:15:18,292 --> 00:15:19,293
Then why…

185
00:15:20,044 --> 00:15:21,546
You do know…

186
00:15:22,380 --> 00:15:24,549
how much I rely on you,

187
00:15:25,633 --> 00:15:27,552
don't you?

188
00:15:28,261 --> 00:15:30,513
M-Me? Y-You rely on me?

189
00:15:34,058 --> 00:15:35,893
I am aware.

190
00:15:35,977 --> 00:15:38,229
With that in mind,

191
00:15:39,147 --> 00:15:42,024
may I ask a small, secret favor

192
00:15:42,608 --> 00:15:43,985
of you?

193
00:15:44,068 --> 00:15:46,529
A secret favor?

194
00:15:46,612 --> 00:15:48,030
Secret.

195
00:15:58,374 --> 00:15:59,792
W-W-Why? What's wrong?

196
00:15:59,876 --> 00:16:02,503
You're so out of it.
What are you even looking at?

197
00:16:03,379 --> 00:16:05,173
What did she say?

198
00:16:06,382 --> 00:16:08,634
-She's getting married.
-Huh?

199
00:16:15,725 --> 00:16:18,394
Right… Wait, she's getting married?

200
00:16:18,477 --> 00:16:19,520
Mom.

201
00:16:20,062 --> 00:16:23,024
You know that uncle
you mentioned last time?

202
00:16:23,107 --> 00:16:24,192
Yeah.

203
00:16:24,275 --> 00:16:26,402
Not the one who went to jail.
I don't like him!

204
00:16:30,281 --> 00:16:32,575
The one who works
at the Royal Secretariat.

205
00:16:32,658 --> 00:16:33,701
Yes, that's right.

206
00:16:34,202 --> 00:16:36,746
Do you think I could get
his contact information?

207
00:16:39,040 --> 00:16:40,291
Goodness, Reporter Park.

208
00:16:40,374 --> 00:16:42,084
It's me. Have you been well?

209
00:16:42,168 --> 00:16:43,169
Yes, of course.

210
00:16:44,128 --> 00:16:46,130
No, Ms. Seong is doing very well.

211
00:16:46,214 --> 00:16:47,381
Yes, that's right.

212
00:16:47,965 --> 00:16:51,344
So, Reporter Kim,
I heard you are a royal correspondent.

213
00:16:51,427 --> 00:16:52,970
Ah, in that case,

214
00:16:53,596 --> 00:16:56,933
you must have connections
with the Public Affairs Office as well.

215
00:16:57,016 --> 00:16:58,351
Ah…

216
00:16:58,434 --> 00:17:00,102
Yes, that's right.

217
00:17:01,312 --> 00:17:04,023
He's taking some time off,

218
00:17:04,106 --> 00:17:05,608
so no official engagements.

219
00:17:05,691 --> 00:17:08,653
The Royal Guard
accompanies him for all that,

220
00:17:08,736 --> 00:17:11,906
-so he'd be impossible to approach.
-Is that so?

221
00:17:12,406 --> 00:17:13,491
However,

222
00:17:14,158 --> 00:17:16,744
he's bound to have informal engagements.

223
00:17:16,827 --> 00:17:19,956
As it turns out, there are a few spots
he visits frequently.

224
00:17:28,589 --> 00:17:30,383
I've managed to compile

225
00:17:31,759 --> 00:17:32,885
a comprehensive list.

226
00:17:36,430 --> 00:17:38,641
Thank you. I'll let you get back to work.

227
00:17:39,642 --> 00:17:41,018
W-Wait, Ms. Do.

228
00:17:46,315 --> 00:17:49,026
Am I part of Ms. Seong's circle now?

229
00:17:51,737 --> 00:17:53,364
Of course.

230
00:17:53,447 --> 00:17:54,615
Without a doubt.

231
00:17:56,784 --> 00:17:57,868
Ah…

232
00:18:18,806 --> 00:18:19,807
Hyah!

233
00:18:28,524 --> 00:18:30,026
Whoa, whoa…

234
00:18:41,621 --> 00:18:43,748
Hmm?

235
00:18:48,461 --> 00:18:49,795
Hyah!

236
00:18:49,879 --> 00:18:50,880
Hyah!

237
00:18:52,548 --> 00:18:53,674
Seong Huiju?

238
00:18:56,719 --> 00:18:57,845
Hyah!

239
00:19:01,641 --> 00:19:02,850
Whoa…

240
00:19:06,187 --> 00:19:08,189
It's been a while, Your Royal Highness.

241
00:19:09,315 --> 00:19:10,775
I believe it has been two days.

242
00:19:10,858 --> 00:19:11,901
Isn't it odd?

243
00:19:12,401 --> 00:19:14,737
It's only been two days,
but I missed you so much.

244
00:19:16,656 --> 00:19:19,617
Why ride here
and not at the Royal Riding Grounds?

245
00:19:19,700 --> 00:19:21,035
It is too confined there.

246
00:19:24,246 --> 00:19:25,956
You could feel confined here too.

247
00:19:32,171 --> 00:19:33,631
Hyah!

248
00:19:41,180 --> 00:19:42,181
Hyah!

249
00:19:59,865 --> 00:20:00,991
I missed you.

250
00:20:01,492 --> 00:20:03,953
Even though I saw you yesterday.

251
00:20:07,665 --> 00:20:10,793
But why are you having breakfast here
and not the Royal Dining Hall?

252
00:20:12,336 --> 00:20:14,755
-I am taking some time off.
-Oh…

253
00:20:15,756 --> 00:20:17,133
Me too.

254
00:20:21,011 --> 00:20:22,888
Are you off to volunteer
at the cat shelter?

255
00:20:22,972 --> 00:20:24,432
To see Taekwon and Taegeuk?

256
00:20:26,267 --> 00:20:28,144
You dared to run a background check on me?

257
00:20:28,227 --> 00:20:29,687
-Yes.
-"Yes"?

258
00:20:30,271 --> 00:20:32,064
You said you wanted to marry for love.

259
00:20:33,315 --> 00:20:34,316
So?

260
00:20:34,400 --> 00:20:35,651
So…

261
00:20:36,861 --> 00:20:38,237
that is why I dare

262
00:20:39,071 --> 00:20:40,072
to make a play

263
00:20:41,407 --> 00:20:42,867
for Your Royal Highness's heart.

264
00:21:13,022 --> 00:21:14,982
I missed you!

265
00:21:15,065 --> 00:21:16,108
Where are you…

266
00:21:28,287 --> 00:21:30,206
You can enjoy the movie.

267
00:21:31,499 --> 00:21:33,542
I'll just enjoy watching you.

268
00:21:48,682 --> 00:21:49,892
I missed you.

269
00:21:50,684 --> 00:21:51,769
Should we run together?

270
00:21:54,230 --> 00:21:55,231
Oh!

271
00:22:00,945 --> 00:22:02,196
You're pretty fast!

272
00:22:10,496 --> 00:22:12,331
-What do you think?
-About what?

273
00:22:12,915 --> 00:22:15,584
The outfit I am wearing right now.

274
00:22:15,668 --> 00:22:18,045
Well, it's not bad…

275
00:22:18,128 --> 00:22:20,256
"It's not bad"? That simply won't do.

276
00:22:20,339 --> 00:22:21,799
What do you mean?

277
00:22:22,383 --> 00:22:25,469
Just keeps popping up out of nowhere.

278
00:22:25,553 --> 00:22:28,013
What keeps popping up out of nowhere?

279
00:22:28,722 --> 00:22:30,057
I must have new garments made.

280
00:22:30,140 --> 00:22:31,642
What? All of a sudden?

281
00:22:31,725 --> 00:22:35,062
If I'm shadowed at every turn,
shouldn't I appear flawless at every step?

282
00:22:35,145 --> 00:22:36,647
Wait, so who's shadowing you?

283
00:22:37,147 --> 00:22:38,315
Get in.

284
00:22:38,399 --> 00:22:39,984
Am I just talking to myself?

285
00:22:52,621 --> 00:22:53,664
GREMLIN

286
00:22:53,747 --> 00:22:56,250
What a crappy way to start the day.

287
00:23:01,297 --> 00:23:02,298
What is it?

288
00:23:02,381 --> 00:23:04,592
Huiju, you haven't forgotten
what today is, right?

289
00:23:04,675 --> 00:23:06,010
I definitely did.

290
00:23:06,093 --> 00:23:08,137
That's why I'm calling to remind you.

291
00:23:08,220 --> 00:23:10,431
You have your arranged date today.

292
00:23:11,432 --> 00:23:13,517
Listen, Dayeong…

293
00:23:14,685 --> 00:23:16,604
I guess Father has high hopes for today.

294
00:23:16,687 --> 00:23:20,941
He insisted that I go to your place
to help you with your outfit and makeup.

295
00:23:21,025 --> 00:23:24,153
I spent ages trying to talk him out
of putting that pressure on you.

296
00:23:24,236 --> 00:23:26,864
How incredibly thoughtful of you.

297
00:23:26,947 --> 00:23:28,365
I know, right?

298
00:23:28,449 --> 00:23:30,743
Huiju, do you think you'll need my help?

299
00:23:30,826 --> 00:23:32,453
I can head over there right now.

300
00:23:32,536 --> 00:23:35,039
Yeah, you should go.
She's going to need a lot of help.

301
00:23:35,122 --> 00:23:36,957
-Taeju?
-You heard that?

302
00:23:38,125 --> 00:23:41,003
What are you doing?
Shouldn't you be at work by now?

303
00:23:41,086 --> 00:23:44,882
Huiju, I'll text you his number
and the meeting place again.

304
00:23:44,965 --> 00:23:45,966
Be sure to check!

305
00:23:46,050 --> 00:23:47,343
You know if you bail on him,

306
00:23:47,426 --> 00:23:50,012
you'll put both Father and me
in a tough spot, right?

307
00:23:54,266 --> 00:23:56,685
Geez, this damn Gremlin is unbelievable.

308
00:24:00,105 --> 00:24:03,776
Father is threatening to shut
down Castle Beauty if you bail again,

309
00:24:03,859 --> 00:24:04,985
so watch out!

310
00:24:05,569 --> 00:24:06,820
P.S. Kim Yeonjun.

311
00:24:06,904 --> 00:24:09,365
Height, 180 cm.
I hear he's really handsome too.

312
00:24:15,704 --> 00:24:16,789
Mr. Kim Yeonjun?

313
00:24:17,289 --> 00:24:19,541
My apologies for the last-minute changes.

314
00:24:19,625 --> 00:24:21,752
I wanted to take care of this quickly.

315
00:24:21,835 --> 00:24:24,171
Not at all. I know how busy you are.

316
00:24:26,757 --> 00:24:29,301
I heard a lot about you from my father.

317
00:24:30,260 --> 00:24:31,261
Really?

318
00:24:31,762 --> 00:24:32,763
Yes, I heard

319
00:24:33,347 --> 00:24:35,307
that you possess both beauty and brains.

320
00:24:37,893 --> 00:24:40,938
And that you have
a deep appreciation for art as well.

321
00:24:41,021 --> 00:24:42,982
Hmm… I do?

322
00:24:43,607 --> 00:24:46,068
Yes, don't you run an arts foundation?

323
00:24:46,151 --> 00:24:47,861
Brilliantly, might I add.

324
00:24:47,945 --> 00:24:48,988
Oh, that?

325
00:24:49,738 --> 00:24:51,991
That's for money laundering purposes.

326
00:24:52,950 --> 00:24:54,284
Brilliantly so.

327
00:24:55,577 --> 00:24:56,578
Pardon?

328
00:24:59,123 --> 00:25:00,249
You know.

329
00:25:04,670 --> 00:25:06,505
When should we hold the wedding?

330
00:25:07,297 --> 00:25:09,174
September? October?

331
00:25:13,387 --> 00:25:14,930
Pardon?

332
00:25:15,014 --> 00:25:17,349
It's an arranged marriage anyway.

333
00:25:17,433 --> 00:25:18,934
No reason to prolong it.

334
00:25:19,018 --> 00:25:20,102
I see.

335
00:25:21,770 --> 00:25:23,105
But shouldn't we at least--

336
00:25:23,188 --> 00:25:24,773
Do you have siblings?

337
00:25:25,899 --> 00:25:26,942
Only son?

338
00:25:27,735 --> 00:25:28,736
Yes, I am.

339
00:25:29,528 --> 00:25:30,529
I'm an only child.

340
00:25:30,612 --> 00:25:31,864
Mmm…

341
00:25:31,947 --> 00:25:32,948
That's nice.

342
00:25:33,991 --> 00:25:36,452
No siblings to fight over the inheritance.

343
00:25:39,413 --> 00:25:41,165
PRIVATE COLLECTION OF
GRAND PRINCE I-AN

344
00:25:49,298 --> 00:25:51,216
I have an older brother.

345
00:25:52,926 --> 00:25:54,511
You know Director Seong Taeju?

346
00:25:55,012 --> 00:25:57,514
Yes, I met him last time
at a shareholders' meeting.

347
00:25:57,598 --> 00:26:01,685
My father simply adores him.

348
00:26:01,769 --> 00:26:03,979
He'll likely succeed
my father as chairman.

349
00:26:04,730 --> 00:26:06,482
And you're a part of that plan.

350
00:26:07,399 --> 00:26:08,400
Me?

351
00:26:08,901 --> 00:26:10,110
How am I a part of that?

352
00:26:10,194 --> 00:26:11,904
He doesn't want to give me leverage.

353
00:26:12,905 --> 00:26:14,782
I'm already good at my job.

354
00:26:15,449 --> 00:26:18,327
He knows if I marry
into a powerful family on top of that,

355
00:26:18,410 --> 00:26:20,788
the first thing I'll do is
kick my brother to the curb.

356
00:26:22,206 --> 00:26:23,791
I see.

357
00:26:28,045 --> 00:26:30,130
PRIVATE COLLECTION OF
GRAND PRINCE I-AN

358
00:26:30,214 --> 00:26:32,508
Is he a cat lover or something?

359
00:26:39,515 --> 00:26:40,808
Do you think you can do it?

360
00:26:41,642 --> 00:26:43,977
-Pardon?
-If you're interested in marrying me,

361
00:26:44,645 --> 00:26:46,939
money must be what you're after.

362
00:26:47,898 --> 00:26:49,441
I can do that.

363
00:26:50,734 --> 00:26:52,653
Whatever sum you have in mind,

364
00:26:53,403 --> 00:26:55,364
I can give you far more than that.

365
00:26:56,615 --> 00:26:59,493
What about you? Can you do your part?

366
00:26:59,576 --> 00:27:02,121
Are you willing to devote
all of yourself to me…

367
00:27:09,253 --> 00:27:11,088
so I can get all the way to the top?

368
00:27:14,049 --> 00:27:15,050
Ms. Seong?

369
00:27:16,260 --> 00:27:17,261
Aide Choi.

370
00:27:17,344 --> 00:27:19,721
-Hello.
-Hello there.

371
00:27:19,805 --> 00:27:21,473
You must be here for the exhibit.

372
00:27:21,557 --> 00:27:24,893
Yes. I wanted to see for myself
how impressive the Royal Collection was.

373
00:27:24,977 --> 00:27:26,770
I see. Is it to your liking?

374
00:27:28,689 --> 00:27:29,773
It's not bad.

375
00:27:29,857 --> 00:27:31,358
I'd steal a few if I could.

376
00:27:31,441 --> 00:27:33,777
Then you should go to basement level two.

377
00:27:33,861 --> 00:27:36,321
The expensive stuff is there.

378
00:27:36,405 --> 00:27:37,531
Aide Choi.

379
00:27:38,115 --> 00:27:39,241
Coming.

380
00:27:39,324 --> 00:27:40,617
Please excuse me.

381
00:27:40,701 --> 00:27:41,952
Enjoy the exhibit.

382
00:27:47,249 --> 00:27:50,043
I'm sorry. I should've introduced you.

383
00:27:54,298 --> 00:27:55,299
Huiju.

384
00:28:05,392 --> 00:28:07,394
I don't think this marriage would work.

385
00:28:09,980 --> 00:28:11,773
Not the least bit surprised.

386
00:28:25,245 --> 00:28:27,623
-Who?
-Ms. Seong Huiju.

387
00:28:27,706 --> 00:28:29,207
The one who proposed to you.

388
00:28:30,375 --> 00:28:33,253
Gosh, as soon as you turned her down,

389
00:28:33,337 --> 00:28:34,880
she found herself a new man.

390
00:28:34,963 --> 00:28:37,466
She's so cool. So cool.

391
00:28:41,887 --> 00:28:46,141
To be honest, I was worried she might be
one of the Queen Mother's people.

392
00:28:46,224 --> 00:28:47,601
You have quite the imagination.

393
00:28:48,268 --> 00:28:49,519
Her Majesty and Seong Huiju?

394
00:28:49,603 --> 00:28:51,229
Why not? It's a possibility.

395
00:28:51,313 --> 00:28:52,856
"Why not"?

396
00:28:54,733 --> 00:28:56,234
Move it more to the right.

397
00:28:57,611 --> 00:28:59,071
More to the right?

398
00:29:01,114 --> 00:29:02,115
Up.

399
00:29:02,199 --> 00:29:03,283
Down.

400
00:29:03,367 --> 00:29:05,243
Up, up, down.

401
00:29:07,955 --> 00:29:09,039
Original spot.

402
00:29:13,752 --> 00:29:16,797
My sister-in-law hails from a family
that has produced four queens.

403
00:29:18,882 --> 00:29:21,009
Few people truly grasp
how towering that pride

404
00:29:22,094 --> 00:29:23,512
and sense of superiority is.

405
00:29:24,846 --> 00:29:25,847
A person like her,

406
00:29:26,723 --> 00:29:28,767
colluding with Huiju, a mere commoner?

407
00:29:33,855 --> 00:29:36,191
Who would win between the two?

408
00:29:38,568 --> 00:29:39,695
Well, you see…

409
00:29:41,154 --> 00:29:42,906
I did a little digging into Ms. Seong.

410
00:29:42,990 --> 00:29:44,074
-Choi Hyeon.
-I mean,

411
00:29:44,157 --> 00:29:46,076
it wasn't a proper investigation
or anything.

412
00:29:46,159 --> 00:29:48,662
It was just a light inquiry.

413
00:29:50,080 --> 00:29:52,749
You have to admit
it was a bit strange.

414
00:29:52,833 --> 00:29:55,002
She just showed up out of nowhere
and proposed.

415
00:29:55,085 --> 00:29:56,712
-So?
-I found that

416
00:29:56,795 --> 00:29:58,213
there was nothing special to note.

417
00:29:58,296 --> 00:30:01,383
She only leaves the house to go to work.

418
00:30:01,466 --> 00:30:03,593
She doesn't seem to have
too many friends either.

419
00:30:03,677 --> 00:30:06,221
She eats with her assistant
and goes to the movies with her.

420
00:30:06,304 --> 00:30:07,597
Wait!

421
00:30:07,681 --> 00:30:09,182
Maybe it's because of her temper?

422
00:30:10,058 --> 00:30:12,060
-Her temper?
-You didn't know?

423
00:30:12,144 --> 00:30:14,479
I heard she was known
for being a hothead in school.

424
00:30:14,563 --> 00:30:17,399
It's harder to find someone
who hasn't fought her.

425
00:30:19,109 --> 00:30:20,986
I hear she never lost a fight either.

426
00:30:22,904 --> 00:30:23,905
Aren't you curious?

427
00:30:25,115 --> 00:30:26,116
About what?

428
00:30:26,199 --> 00:30:29,244
As you said,
the Queen Mother and Ms. Seong

429
00:30:29,327 --> 00:30:30,954
could not be any more different.

430
00:30:31,038 --> 00:30:33,915
Of course, if rank is in play,
the outcome is obvious.

431
00:30:33,999 --> 00:30:36,376
But strip away the hierarchy?

432
00:30:36,460 --> 00:30:38,170
It'll be like "Pow!" With a bit of…

433
00:30:43,300 --> 00:30:44,342
My apologies.

434
00:31:14,706 --> 00:31:16,958
Have you truly gone mad?

435
00:31:26,885 --> 00:31:30,097
I INTEND TO STEP DOWN
FROM THE THRONE…

436
00:31:48,532 --> 00:31:50,450
It will be better than dying.

437
00:32:00,460 --> 00:32:02,295
It would be better to die.

438
00:32:07,134 --> 00:32:08,593
I would rather see you dead.

439
00:32:18,395 --> 00:32:20,355
For the sake of the Crown Prince.

440
00:32:33,743 --> 00:32:34,744
My Queen.

441
00:32:49,426 --> 00:32:51,052
My Queen!

442
00:32:54,347 --> 00:32:56,266
-Fire!
-It's a fire!

443
00:33:18,997 --> 00:33:21,166
-Your Majesty!
-Your Majesty!

444
00:33:21,249 --> 00:33:23,793
Your Majesty…

445
00:33:25,045 --> 00:33:26,296
Your Majesty…

446
00:33:27,422 --> 00:33:28,757
Your Majesty…

447
00:33:54,532 --> 00:33:56,117
Where is the Crown Prince?

448
00:33:56,743 --> 00:33:57,744
Huh?

449
00:33:58,578 --> 00:34:00,205
Where is my nephew…

450
00:34:02,332 --> 00:34:03,750
the heir to the throne?

451
00:34:46,793 --> 00:34:48,253
Did you sleep poorly again?

452
00:34:59,764 --> 00:35:02,183
You can't keep going without sleep.

453
00:35:09,858 --> 00:35:12,736
Do you know what you will
be doing today, Your Majesty?

454
00:35:13,403 --> 00:35:15,780
I am to present the Flowers of Honor.

455
00:35:16,364 --> 00:35:20,118
The recipients are your valued subjects
who lead the nation's industries.

456
00:35:20,744 --> 00:35:22,912
They are Your Majesty's trusty workhorses.

457
00:35:23,413 --> 00:35:24,414
Hence,

458
00:35:25,707 --> 00:35:27,626
you must carry yourself with dignity.

459
00:35:31,212 --> 00:35:33,089
When is I-AN set to return?

460
00:35:33,173 --> 00:35:35,342
I believe he is to return in four days.

461
00:35:37,260 --> 00:35:38,386
This is your opportunity.

462
00:35:38,470 --> 00:35:40,972
You must show the world
you can do it on your own.

463
00:35:41,056 --> 00:35:43,016
Without I-AN by your side.

464
00:35:43,725 --> 00:35:45,101
Do you understand?

465
00:35:47,395 --> 00:35:48,396
Yes.

466
00:35:53,193 --> 00:35:54,277
He'll be fine, right?

467
00:35:54,778 --> 00:35:55,945
No, he won't.

468
00:35:56,029 --> 00:35:58,490
How can you say that? You're his uncle.

469
00:35:59,199 --> 00:36:00,492
I know because I'm his uncle.

470
00:36:01,576 --> 00:36:04,579
I know that my nephew is but a mere child.

471
00:36:05,205 --> 00:36:08,750
Then perhaps you can go
and lend him your support.

472
00:36:10,460 --> 00:36:13,088
-Why should I?
-You said he is just a child.

473
00:36:14,214 --> 00:36:15,632
Why are you sweating so much?

474
00:36:16,466 --> 00:36:17,550
Are you feeling unwell?

475
00:36:21,554 --> 00:36:23,890
Yes, I'm listening.

476
00:36:25,934 --> 00:36:28,186
All right, I get it.

477
00:36:30,271 --> 00:36:31,856
DOBBY

478
00:36:31,940 --> 00:36:34,567
You have to be
at the venue by 11,

479
00:36:34,651 --> 00:36:36,111
so no dawdling please.

480
00:36:36,194 --> 00:36:37,821
Have you eaten?

481
00:36:37,904 --> 00:36:40,365
You won't have time to eat,
so eat something beforehand.

482
00:36:40,907 --> 00:36:42,742
There will be reporters everywhere.

483
00:36:42,826 --> 00:36:44,411
A lot of eyes will be on you.

484
00:36:44,494 --> 00:36:46,079
You know if you cause a scene,

485
00:36:46,162 --> 00:36:47,872
I'll be stuck working all night, right?

486
00:36:48,915 --> 00:36:51,126
Your dry-cleaned outfit is on the hanger.

487
00:36:52,711 --> 00:36:54,087
No red.

488
00:36:58,174 --> 00:36:59,592
No strong perfume.

489
00:37:02,887 --> 00:37:06,015
No flashy accessories. Got it?

490
00:37:06,808 --> 00:37:09,185
I bought you for this exact purpose.

491
00:37:09,269 --> 00:37:11,354
Don't even. I told you nothing flashy.

492
00:37:12,897 --> 00:37:14,190
Are we on a video call?

493
00:37:43,762 --> 00:37:46,598
2025 ECONOMIC HONORS OF KOREA

494
00:37:50,518 --> 00:37:52,604
This is how they treat their honorees?

495
00:37:53,313 --> 00:37:55,648
Lower your voice.
There are lots of reporters around.

496
00:37:55,732 --> 00:37:58,860
Seriously? If anything,
they should be boosting my morale.

497
00:37:58,943 --> 00:38:00,195
Are they trying to crush it?

498
00:38:00,278 --> 00:38:02,947
His Majesty the King is coming.
What choice do we have?

499
00:38:03,031 --> 00:38:04,866
Right, so why did he need to be here?

500
00:38:04,949 --> 00:38:06,409
Just enjoy cookies at the palace.

501
00:38:06,493 --> 00:38:07,911
-Stop it.
-All right!

502
00:38:18,588 --> 00:38:19,839
Your Majesty.

503
00:38:19,923 --> 00:38:21,800
You do not need to be nervous.

504
00:38:21,883 --> 00:38:25,011
You have us by your side.

505
00:38:25,678 --> 00:38:27,180
Would Your Majesty like a snack?

506
00:38:28,181 --> 00:38:31,935
Can we review the order
of the ceremony again?

507
00:38:32,644 --> 00:38:36,064
Looking at that
will only make you more nervous.

508
00:38:36,147 --> 00:38:38,900
Once you step up onto the podium,
we'll take care of everything.

509
00:38:42,904 --> 00:38:43,905
Your Majesty.

510
00:38:46,908 --> 00:38:47,909
Your Royal Highness.

511
00:38:52,163 --> 00:38:53,206
What brings you here?

512
00:38:54,749 --> 00:38:56,459
You dare stand in my way?

513
00:38:58,127 --> 00:38:59,462
No, I wasn't…

514
00:38:59,546 --> 00:39:01,714
Then do you stand in His Majesty's way?

515
00:39:11,683 --> 00:39:13,560
The aides have been
negligent in their duties.

516
00:39:15,144 --> 00:39:17,438
Both protocol and security
are woefully inadequate.

517
00:39:18,481 --> 00:39:20,149
My apologies, Your Royal Highness.

518
00:39:23,611 --> 00:39:26,614
INCOMING CALL

519
00:39:36,916 --> 00:39:38,126
Your Majesty.

520
00:39:38,209 --> 00:39:39,502
Uncle.

521
00:39:41,421 --> 00:39:43,464
I am scared, Uncle.

522
00:39:58,187 --> 00:39:59,272
Thus,

523
00:39:59,898 --> 00:40:03,151
I have come to fulfill my duty
as your loyal subject, Your Majesty.

524
00:40:11,910 --> 00:40:15,330
Announcing His Majesty!

525
00:40:48,571 --> 00:40:50,239
Take my hand, Your Majesty.

526
00:41:22,063 --> 00:41:24,190
Next, we have
the Global Entrepreneur Award.

527
00:41:24,273 --> 00:41:27,443
Chairman Park Jeseung.
Please give him a warm round of applause.

528
00:41:36,285 --> 00:41:39,288
Next, we have the Best Entrepreneur Award.

529
00:41:39,372 --> 00:41:43,418
Castle Beauty's Seong Huiju.

530
00:41:45,586 --> 00:41:49,007
Castle Beauty remains at the forefront
of the global K-beauty craze,

531
00:41:49,090 --> 00:41:52,927
showcasing Korea's advanced technology
and refined beauty.

532
00:41:53,011 --> 00:41:54,679
Guided by the slogan "Eco Beauty,"

533
00:41:54,762 --> 00:41:58,016
they remain dedicated
to creating eco-friendly products.

534
00:42:02,562 --> 00:42:03,563
Your Majesty.

535
00:42:04,063 --> 00:42:05,690
Can you place it on my head?

536
00:42:07,817 --> 00:42:08,901
Right here.

537
00:42:18,161 --> 00:42:19,954
I am deeply honored, Your Majesty.

538
00:42:26,044 --> 00:42:27,503
The nation rejoices

539
00:42:28,379 --> 00:42:29,797
in the beauty of your talent.

540
00:42:32,884 --> 00:42:34,093
I missed you.

541
00:42:37,263 --> 00:42:39,307
Will there be a prize as well?

542
00:42:41,100 --> 00:42:42,727
I believe it is already on your head.

543
00:42:43,895 --> 00:42:45,897
This is from His Majesty.

544
00:42:46,606 --> 00:42:48,232
There is something else I would like

545
00:42:49,358 --> 00:42:50,735
from Your Royal Highness.

546
00:42:55,114 --> 00:42:57,450
She is a young leader
representing the nation.

547
00:42:57,533 --> 00:43:01,162
CEO Seong Huiju.
Please give her a warm round of applause.

548
00:43:27,939 --> 00:43:28,940
Ready?

549
00:43:35,279 --> 00:43:36,531
-Got it?
-Yes, got it.

550
00:43:36,614 --> 00:43:37,615
Okay.

551
00:43:40,701 --> 00:43:43,913
"Hashtag Flower of Honor."

552
00:43:44,497 --> 00:43:46,249
"Best Company."

553
00:43:46,332 --> 00:43:48,417
"Castle Beauty."

554
00:43:48,501 --> 00:43:50,336
"Hashtag…

555
00:43:52,755 --> 00:43:55,174
Grand Prince I-AN."

556
00:43:57,677 --> 00:43:59,262
Let's go.

557
00:44:02,014 --> 00:44:03,099
PRIME MINISTER MIN JEONGWOO

558
00:44:03,182 --> 00:44:05,434
Come in.

559
00:44:10,690 --> 00:44:11,691
Sir.

560
00:44:11,774 --> 00:44:13,526
The Economic Honors event went smoothly.

561
00:44:14,402 --> 00:44:15,403
Really?

562
00:44:16,112 --> 00:44:18,322
Our young Sovereign is all grown up now.

563
00:44:18,948 --> 00:44:21,242
Grand Prince I-AN accompanied him.

564
00:44:22,243 --> 00:44:23,953
-Isn't he on leave?
-Yes.

565
00:44:24,036 --> 00:44:27,165
It was a last-minute decision
after His Majesty made a personal request.

566
00:44:27,248 --> 00:44:28,708
Hmm…

567
00:44:33,045 --> 00:44:34,297
PRINCE I-AN'S
SURPRISE APPEARANCE

568
00:44:34,380 --> 00:44:35,506
AT 2025 ECONOMIC HONORS…

569
00:44:39,302 --> 00:44:42,013
CASTLE BEAUTY'S SEONG HUIJU
RECEIVES BEST ENTREPRENEUR AWARD

570
00:44:48,186 --> 00:44:50,062
Are you going somewhere?

571
00:44:50,146 --> 00:44:51,480
I'm clocking out.

572
00:44:51,564 --> 00:44:52,982
Already?

573
00:44:53,065 --> 00:44:54,066
I'm done.

574
00:44:58,446 --> 00:45:00,656
And maybe a bit quicker next time.

575
00:45:01,574 --> 00:45:02,575
Pardon?

576
00:45:02,658 --> 00:45:04,952
If you tell me after the fact,
where does that leave me?

577
00:45:07,038 --> 00:45:08,748
My apologies, sir.

578
00:45:22,511 --> 00:45:23,888
Get back safely, Your Majesty.

579
00:45:24,472 --> 00:45:27,099
Are you not coming with me?

580
00:45:28,142 --> 00:45:30,228
I am still on leave.

581
00:45:31,896 --> 00:45:34,732
Your Majesty, the Queen Mother is waiting.

582
00:46:03,761 --> 00:46:04,762
Are you all right?

583
00:46:08,849 --> 00:46:10,017
Take this.

584
00:46:11,352 --> 00:46:12,353
This too.

585
00:46:13,896 --> 00:46:16,774
-Wait, hold on. Give me that too.
-Why?

586
00:46:16,857 --> 00:46:19,777
Are you actually wearing that hat
to your hotel staycation?

587
00:46:19,860 --> 00:46:21,112
-Yeah.
-Seriously?

588
00:46:22,989 --> 00:46:25,199
Don't tell people
you're the CEO of Castle Beauty.

589
00:46:26,701 --> 00:46:29,578
They all know already.

590
00:46:30,663 --> 00:46:32,415
Don't call me unless it's urgent.

591
00:46:32,498 --> 00:46:34,375
It's been ages since I've had time off.

592
00:46:35,001 --> 00:46:37,753
Me too. Me too.

593
00:46:37,837 --> 00:46:39,255
-Go.
-I'm off.

594
00:46:42,341 --> 00:46:43,342
Seong Huiju.

595
00:46:45,011 --> 00:46:46,095
Oh.

596
00:46:46,178 --> 00:46:47,179
Jeongwoo.

597
00:46:57,148 --> 00:46:58,441
Order everything.

598
00:46:58,524 --> 00:47:00,234
I am a winner of the Flower of Honor.

599
00:47:00,318 --> 00:47:02,236
It'll be my treat today.

600
00:47:03,821 --> 00:47:04,822
No.

601
00:47:04,905 --> 00:47:07,241
Let me treat you today
to congratulate you.

602
00:47:07,325 --> 00:47:09,118
I told you I'd treat you last time.

603
00:47:10,161 --> 00:47:12,913
Now that's an offer I never turn down.

604
00:47:12,997 --> 00:47:14,123
Score.

605
00:47:17,626 --> 00:47:18,753
Hmm…

606
00:47:23,382 --> 00:47:26,510
Just take it off for the meal.

607
00:47:26,594 --> 00:47:27,678
Why?

608
00:47:28,262 --> 00:47:30,014
Jealous?

609
00:47:30,097 --> 00:47:31,766
It's embarrassing.

610
00:47:32,350 --> 00:47:33,768
You look like a giant pineapple.

611
00:47:35,227 --> 00:47:37,646
Are you sure
it's not a really pretty pineapple?

612
00:47:38,230 --> 00:47:39,315
Definitely not.

613
00:47:57,333 --> 00:47:59,627
Moments like this remind me
you haven't changed at all.

614
00:47:59,710 --> 00:48:01,504
What do you mean?

615
00:48:01,587 --> 00:48:04,465
You used to get the Flower of Honor
all the time in school.

616
00:48:04,548 --> 00:48:07,426
For your grades and artwork…

617
00:48:09,220 --> 00:48:10,388
What else was there?

618
00:48:11,972 --> 00:48:13,099
Archery?

619
00:48:13,974 --> 00:48:15,393
Archery.

620
00:48:27,363 --> 00:48:30,533
How were you even chosen
to represent Jujak House?

621
00:48:30,616 --> 00:48:33,369
I had to change my grip yesterday…

622
00:48:34,286 --> 00:48:35,746
Activate your core.

623
00:48:36,831 --> 00:48:38,499
Chin down.

624
00:48:38,582 --> 00:48:39,583
Chest.

625
00:48:40,209 --> 00:48:41,210
Chest.

626
00:48:43,421 --> 00:48:44,422
Draw your bow.

627
00:48:50,094 --> 00:48:51,679
Shoulders back further.

628
00:48:55,850 --> 00:48:56,934
Right by your lips.

629
00:49:02,815 --> 00:49:03,816
Focus!

630
00:49:04,900 --> 00:49:06,527
Right. Focus.

631
00:49:07,820 --> 00:49:09,905
I swear

632
00:49:11,240 --> 00:49:14,702
there will be hell to pay
if we lose because of you.

633
00:49:16,620 --> 00:49:18,330
-Focus!
-Huh?

634
00:49:19,248 --> 00:49:20,624
Right, focus.

635
00:49:21,125 --> 00:49:22,293
Keep pulling

636
00:49:23,377 --> 00:49:24,378
and shoot.

637
00:49:25,379 --> 00:49:29,258
Thank goodness
you were at least book smart.

638
00:49:29,842 --> 00:49:31,552
-Me?
-You're bad at everything else.

639
00:49:31,635 --> 00:49:34,096
Seriously? Me?

640
00:49:34,180 --> 00:49:37,933
You're not like running the country
into the ground or anything, right?

641
00:49:39,018 --> 00:49:40,728
If something feels off,

642
00:49:40,811 --> 00:49:43,481
don't be afraid to ask questions.
No need to feel embarrassed.

643
00:49:43,564 --> 00:49:45,024
Don't try to do it alone.

644
00:49:45,107 --> 00:49:46,275
All right.

645
00:49:46,984 --> 00:49:48,152
Just order already.

646
00:49:51,155 --> 00:49:53,782
Let's see here.

647
00:49:56,118 --> 00:49:59,121
What should I have?

648
00:50:03,042 --> 00:50:04,627
PHARMACY

649
00:50:07,004 --> 00:50:08,088
Hello.

650
00:50:08,172 --> 00:50:09,215
Welcome.

651
00:50:09,298 --> 00:50:12,009
What should someone take
if they have a really bad headache,

652
00:50:12,092 --> 00:50:14,470
a slight fever,
and keep breaking out in a cold sweat?

653
00:50:14,553 --> 00:50:16,555
Just a moment. I'll grab what you need.

654
00:50:16,639 --> 00:50:18,891
Okay. Please hurry.

655
00:50:39,537 --> 00:50:40,538
Your Royal Highness.

656
00:50:50,881 --> 00:50:51,882
Once the fever breaks,

657
00:50:51,966 --> 00:50:53,884
we should take you
to Royal Seoul Hospital.

658
00:50:53,968 --> 00:50:56,178
I think it'd be best
to have you checked out there.

659
00:50:57,513 --> 00:50:59,640
It's crawling
with the Queen Mother's brothers.

660
00:50:59,723 --> 00:51:01,392
Don't stir up trouble.

661
00:51:01,934 --> 00:51:04,144
Understood.

662
00:51:04,228 --> 00:51:05,563
Have you notified my household?

663
00:51:06,313 --> 00:51:07,314
Yes.

664
00:51:07,398 --> 00:51:09,650
I told them you'd be
staying the night at a hotel.

665
00:51:09,733 --> 00:51:12,236
I didn't say anything
about you being sick. Don't worry.

666
00:51:21,245 --> 00:51:23,038
The doors are opening.

667
00:51:27,710 --> 00:51:29,545
SHE LOOKS SO DAMN GOOD

668
00:51:29,628 --> 00:51:32,423
Our stock is going to skyrocket tomorrow.

669
00:51:34,341 --> 00:51:35,384
Oh, my goodness.

670
00:51:35,467 --> 00:51:36,468
Oh, my.

671
00:51:37,094 --> 00:51:38,721
-Ms. Seong?
-Aide Choi?

672
00:51:39,263 --> 00:51:40,723
-Hello.
-Yes, hello.

673
00:51:51,025 --> 00:51:52,568
You don't need to worry too much.

674
00:51:53,444 --> 00:51:57,573
However, I do wonder
if he typically has trouble sleeping.

675
00:51:58,407 --> 00:51:59,408
Uh…

676
00:51:59,992 --> 00:52:03,245
Yes, he suffers from a bit of insomnia.

677
00:52:03,329 --> 00:52:06,749
It's hard to recover from fatigue
if you can't sleep.

678
00:52:07,458 --> 00:52:09,918
Sleeping aids should help.

679
00:52:10,002 --> 00:52:12,296
Make sure he gets a prescription
and gets some sleep.

680
00:52:12,379 --> 00:52:13,714
All right. Thank you, doctor.

681
00:52:27,895 --> 00:52:29,146
Doctor.

682
00:52:29,730 --> 00:52:31,690
Thank you for coming at a late hour.

683
00:52:31,774 --> 00:52:33,359
No need to thank me.

684
00:52:34,151 --> 00:52:35,194
For the record,

685
00:52:36,362 --> 00:52:38,947
can we say I was the patient today?

686
00:52:39,615 --> 00:52:42,117
-Pardon?
-You know I get hurt all the time.

687
00:52:43,369 --> 00:52:44,995
You were here to see me

688
00:52:45,704 --> 00:52:47,539
and only me today.

689
00:52:51,251 --> 00:52:52,378
Understood, Ms. Seong.

690
00:52:54,129 --> 00:52:55,130
Get back safely.

691
00:52:55,798 --> 00:52:56,799
Take care.

692
00:53:01,345 --> 00:53:02,805
PRINCE I-AN'S
SURPRISE APPEARANCE

693
00:53:02,888 --> 00:53:04,223
AT ECONOMIC HONORS…

694
00:53:13,190 --> 00:53:16,193
Did you forget I told you
to carry yourself with dignity?

695
00:53:16,819 --> 00:53:20,698
U-Uncle…

696
00:53:20,781 --> 00:53:22,366
Do not call him that!

697
00:53:27,830 --> 00:53:30,040
Please do not let it upset you.

698
00:53:30,791 --> 00:53:33,210
His Majesty is still very young.

699
00:53:36,463 --> 00:53:38,716
How truly contemptible.

700
00:53:39,675 --> 00:53:40,676
Pardon?

701
00:53:43,220 --> 00:53:45,264
I speak of that feeble bloodline.

702
00:53:47,266 --> 00:53:51,186
He was the very likeness
of the late king at that moment.

703
00:53:54,231 --> 00:53:55,816
It sends a chill down my spine.

704
00:54:02,948 --> 00:54:04,908
Have you located I-AN?

705
00:54:04,992 --> 00:54:06,744
Yes, Your Majesty.

706
00:54:12,791 --> 00:54:13,792
Aide Choi.

707
00:54:14,460 --> 00:54:15,627
Ms. Seong.

708
00:54:15,711 --> 00:54:17,045
You need to eat.

709
00:54:18,797 --> 00:54:19,965
How about a sandwich?

710
00:54:20,466 --> 00:54:22,384
SUBWAY

711
00:54:28,140 --> 00:54:30,392
I see you really like sandwiches.

712
00:54:32,186 --> 00:54:33,187
Not exactly.

713
00:54:34,021 --> 00:54:37,399
I was so preoccupied earlier
that I didn't get a chance to eat.

714
00:54:37,483 --> 00:54:39,777
And this is really good.

715
00:54:39,860 --> 00:54:40,986
Eat up.

716
00:54:41,069 --> 00:54:43,197
I order this all the time
when I'm working late.

717
00:54:47,493 --> 00:54:48,744
Thank you.

718
00:54:48,827 --> 00:54:50,954
He was just
on the verge of collapse earlier.

719
00:54:51,038 --> 00:54:53,248
My mind went blank.

720
00:54:54,082 --> 00:54:55,792
You were a huge help.

721
00:54:59,505 --> 00:55:01,673
But wouldn't he be better off
returning to the palace?

722
00:55:01,757 --> 00:55:03,300
There are physicians at the palace.

723
00:55:03,383 --> 00:55:06,678
I'm sure that will be more comfortable
than staying in some hotel room.

724
00:55:12,184 --> 00:55:14,394
He despises being the center of attention.

725
00:55:15,103 --> 00:55:16,813
The physicians would freak out
if they knew.

726
00:55:16,897 --> 00:55:19,525
The Royal Medical Institution
would be on standby all day.

727
00:55:20,025 --> 00:55:22,986
The Royal Kitchen would be cooking
all sorts of soups and porridges.

728
00:55:23,070 --> 00:55:26,031
Royal Seoul Hospital would be the same.
It'd be worse if anything.

729
00:55:26,114 --> 00:55:27,241
As soon as he steps inside,

730
00:55:27,324 --> 00:55:30,953
photos will be taken,
and all kinds of rumors will spread.

731
00:55:31,912 --> 00:55:32,913
Hmm…

732
00:55:40,337 --> 00:55:41,338
Oh, no.

733
00:55:42,589 --> 00:55:43,715
-You need to go.
-What?

734
00:55:43,799 --> 00:55:46,343
The Queen Mother is here.

735
00:55:46,426 --> 00:55:48,345
-Get up.
-Who? Mother?

736
00:55:48,428 --> 00:55:50,764
You need to get out of here.
The Queen Mother…

737
00:55:50,847 --> 00:55:53,016
-Where can I hide you? Come on.
-What's going on?

738
00:55:53,100 --> 00:55:55,978
-Where are you taking me?
-You have to be quiet.

739
00:56:00,691 --> 00:56:03,610
You can do this. You got this, Choi Hyeon.

740
00:56:08,031 --> 00:56:10,867
-Your Majesty, what brings you by?
-Step aside.

741
00:56:11,743 --> 00:56:13,287
It is already quite late. Tomorrow…

742
00:56:44,776 --> 00:56:46,528
Tell her I am not yet suitably attired

743
00:56:48,238 --> 00:56:49,448
and that she must wait.

744
00:57:43,251 --> 00:57:45,504
When the day breaks,
get yourself suitably attired

745
00:57:45,587 --> 00:57:47,255
to answer for today's transgression.

746
00:57:50,384 --> 00:57:51,927
That is what you will tell him.

747
00:57:59,351 --> 00:58:00,560
What now?

748
00:58:22,249 --> 00:58:24,418
-Yeah?
-Ms. Seong, where are you?

749
00:58:24,501 --> 00:58:27,879
Ms. Do, do you know
what time it is right now?

750
00:58:27,963 --> 00:58:29,131
Where are you?

751
00:58:30,173 --> 00:58:31,425
At the hotel.

752
00:58:31,508 --> 00:58:33,677
-Stay right there.
-What?

753
00:58:33,760 --> 00:58:35,804
Stay in your room. I'll come to you.

754
00:58:35,887 --> 00:58:36,888
Got it?

755
00:58:40,475 --> 00:58:41,977
What's wrong with her?

756
00:58:46,732 --> 00:58:48,567
PRINCE I-AN SPOTTED
IN SECRET TRYST

757
00:58:48,650 --> 00:58:50,068
WITH CASTLE BEAUTY SEONG HUIJU

758
00:58:52,779 --> 00:58:54,740
WHERE THE ROYAL COUPLE
ENJOYS THEIR TIME OFF…

759
00:58:56,116 --> 00:58:57,325
…A SECRET DATE AT A HOTEL…

760
00:58:57,409 --> 00:58:58,410
ROYAL PAIR ROCKS…

761
00:58:58,493 --> 00:59:00,328
PRINCE I-AN'S SECRET LOVER…

762
00:59:03,123 --> 00:59:04,875
-No, no.
-Yes, Reporter Kim.

763
00:59:04,958 --> 00:59:07,711
-I'll get back to you.
-No, we haven't confirmed anything yet.

764
00:59:07,794 --> 00:59:09,796
-Yes, will do.
-No, not at all.

765
00:59:09,880 --> 00:59:11,173
-Just a moment.
-Hello?

766
00:59:12,507 --> 00:59:14,217
Is Seong Huiju insane?

767
00:59:14,301 --> 00:59:15,969
-Why? What's up?
-Look at this.

768
00:59:18,138 --> 00:59:19,181
WEDDING BELLS…

769
00:59:22,601 --> 00:59:24,102
Oh my goodness!

770
00:59:25,228 --> 00:59:28,482
-Do you think they slept together?
-Of course, they were at a hotel!

771
00:59:31,276 --> 00:59:32,736
Ooh…

772
00:59:32,819 --> 00:59:34,571
What are you so happy about?

773
00:59:34,654 --> 00:59:35,989
What? Are you jealous of her?

774
00:59:37,407 --> 00:59:39,242
You are unbelievable.

775
00:59:42,537 --> 00:59:45,832
Ah… Is that why
she turned down all those dates?

776
00:59:47,667 --> 00:59:48,877
You think so?

777
00:59:51,630 --> 00:59:54,132
"Grand Prince I-AN's secret lover"?

778
00:59:55,926 --> 00:59:56,927
Me?

779
01:00:01,765 --> 01:00:05,268
Pull yourself together, Do Hyejeong.
You've been through far worse.

780
01:00:05,352 --> 01:00:06,728
You got this. Damn it.

781
01:00:06,812 --> 01:00:08,730
Calm down.

782
01:00:08,814 --> 01:00:10,148
Who'd believe this crap?

783
01:00:10,774 --> 01:00:12,734
Why wouldn't they?

784
01:00:12,818 --> 01:00:14,110
Ms. Seong.

785
01:00:14,194 --> 01:00:16,363
Look. They have photos.

786
01:00:17,197 --> 01:00:19,533
Prince I-AN checks in at 4:00 p.m. Snap.

787
01:00:19,616 --> 01:00:22,202
You check in at 7:00 p.m. Snap.

788
01:00:22,285 --> 01:00:23,411
You step out at 9:00 p.m.

789
01:00:23,495 --> 01:00:26,373
to return at 9:30 p.m.
with sandwiches. Snap.

790
01:00:26,456 --> 01:00:29,668
And you can even see
where you got the sandwiches from.

791
01:00:29,751 --> 01:00:31,211
-Really?
-Yes.

792
01:00:31,294 --> 01:00:34,256
Wow. That sandwich place
just hit the jackpot.

793
01:00:34,923 --> 01:00:36,883
They should pay us for the PR.

794
01:00:36,967 --> 01:00:38,468
Ms. Seong.

795
01:00:39,594 --> 01:00:40,720
All right. I hear you.

796
01:00:41,346 --> 01:00:43,473
But I swear nothing happened.

797
01:00:44,057 --> 01:00:46,685
We were with Aide Choi and stuff.

798
01:00:46,768 --> 01:00:48,061
Oh, I see.

799
01:00:48,144 --> 01:00:51,231
Who cares about that
when Aide Choi isn't in a single shot?

800
01:00:51,314 --> 01:00:53,483
Not even a single royal guard.

801
01:00:53,567 --> 01:00:54,901
What a great narrative.

802
01:00:55,527 --> 01:00:57,988
"Prince I-AN Dismisses
Royal Guards for Secret Tryst."

803
01:00:58,071 --> 01:01:00,073
From the riding grounds

804
01:01:00,156 --> 01:01:01,741
to a traditional restaurant,

805
01:01:01,825 --> 01:01:04,077
all sorts of location shoots for you.

806
01:01:06,037 --> 01:01:07,581
SEONGSAN DAILY REPORTER
AN SAEHUN

807
01:01:10,917 --> 01:01:12,252
HAEMYEONG REPORTER JEONG SUJIN

808
01:01:17,007 --> 01:01:19,175
First of all,
why did you call for your doctor?

809
01:01:20,051 --> 01:01:21,094
They got him too?

810
01:01:22,345 --> 01:01:25,056
Thanks to that shot,
they're even speculating you're pregnant.

811
01:01:25,140 --> 01:01:26,933
What?

812
01:01:28,310 --> 01:01:29,311
Wow…

813
01:01:29,394 --> 01:01:32,022
You have to hand it
to the public's imagination.

814
01:01:33,607 --> 01:01:34,941
"A premarital pregnancy"?

815
01:01:35,567 --> 01:01:36,818
Focus!

816
01:01:38,278 --> 01:01:39,279
Focus.

817
01:01:39,905 --> 01:01:41,823
Are you sure it will be all right?

818
01:01:42,949 --> 01:01:45,201
I fear this may bring
dishonor to the Crown.

819
01:01:45,702 --> 01:01:47,245
I am sure it will.

820
01:01:48,204 --> 01:01:50,832
The royal family's dignity
will be cast to the ground…

821
01:01:53,376 --> 01:01:56,671
and this woman will be laid
upon the chopping block and carved up.

822
01:01:57,297 --> 01:01:58,298
That must be why…

823
01:02:00,425 --> 01:02:01,885
they are denying it.

824
01:02:07,974 --> 01:02:09,643
Are you doing this

825
01:02:09,726 --> 01:02:12,312
because you don't know
who Prince I-AN is for the people?

826
01:02:13,229 --> 01:02:15,732
Did you already forget last year
when you dated the leader

827
01:02:15,815 --> 01:02:18,777
of Idol Galaxy or whatever
and got egged when you were caught?

828
01:02:18,860 --> 01:02:20,445
They keyed your car every other day.

829
01:02:20,528 --> 01:02:23,573
You said it was pure torture
dealing with the overzealous fans

830
01:02:23,657 --> 01:02:25,575
who rang your doorbell at dawn
and ran away.

831
01:02:25,659 --> 01:02:27,035
You must remember that.

832
01:02:29,204 --> 01:02:30,872
Prince I-AN isn't an idol star.

833
01:02:31,623 --> 01:02:33,249
He's so much worse.

834
01:02:33,333 --> 01:02:36,211
Idol stars are beloved
by their fandom alone.

835
01:02:36,294 --> 01:02:39,089
Prince I-AN is beloved
by the whole country.

836
01:02:39,172 --> 01:02:40,173
Everyone.

837
01:02:41,716 --> 01:02:42,717
I don't love him.

838
01:02:42,801 --> 01:02:44,010
Ms. Seong!

839
01:02:45,345 --> 01:02:47,514
You're going to scare the baby!

840
01:02:50,684 --> 01:02:52,852
"A premarital pregnancy"?

841
01:02:52,936 --> 01:02:54,062
Unbelievable.

842
01:02:55,188 --> 01:02:56,982
Right. Got it.

843
01:03:09,327 --> 01:03:10,328
GRAND PRINCE

844
01:03:10,412 --> 01:03:12,038
SEONG HUIJU

845
01:03:15,291 --> 01:03:17,544
The caller is unavailable…

846
01:03:19,963 --> 01:03:21,381
Sir.

847
01:03:21,464 --> 01:03:23,842
Still, wouldn't it be best
to contain this quickly?

848
01:03:23,925 --> 01:03:26,386
If people start throwing around
terms like "Royal Risk"…

849
01:03:26,469 --> 01:03:28,805
-It won't be all bad.
-Pardon?

850
01:03:28,888 --> 01:03:32,350
It'll make all the criticism
over the minimum wage freeze disappear.

851
01:03:32,892 --> 01:03:35,395
Leave it for now. It's just a minor fuss.

852
01:03:36,187 --> 01:03:37,188
Yes, sir.

853
01:03:48,950 --> 01:03:50,452
To the palace, please.

854
01:03:51,202 --> 01:03:52,454
To my private residence.

855
01:03:53,621 --> 01:03:55,623
You need to make your way
to the palace first.

856
01:03:55,707 --> 01:03:57,459
Prime Minister Min is already there.

857
01:03:57,542 --> 01:03:59,461
The Public Affairs Office
is also looking--

858
01:03:59,544 --> 01:04:01,337
I said, to my private residence.

859
01:04:03,757 --> 01:04:05,216
Have Seong Huiju…

860
01:04:05,925 --> 01:04:07,093
meet me there.

861
01:04:53,389 --> 01:04:55,350
This way, Ms. Seong.

862
01:05:16,830 --> 01:05:18,206
Am I the only one freaking out?

863
01:05:18,957 --> 01:05:21,084
No. I'm freaking out too.

864
01:05:28,508 --> 01:05:29,801
Only Ms. Seong may go inside.

865
01:05:29,884 --> 01:05:32,345
His Royal Highness asked
for a private meeting.

866
01:05:35,014 --> 01:05:37,267
I'm fine. Just wait for me here.

867
01:05:51,865 --> 01:05:53,616
Is your fever gone?

868
01:05:55,618 --> 01:05:56,911
As you can see.

869
01:05:58,371 --> 01:06:00,290
You're in good spirits.

870
01:06:01,124 --> 01:06:02,500
As you can see.

871
01:06:04,752 --> 01:06:07,172
I missed you.
Even though I saw you yesterday.

872
01:06:16,055 --> 01:06:17,223
Let me apologize

873
01:06:18,183 --> 01:06:19,809
for dragging you into this scandal

874
01:06:19,893 --> 01:06:22,562
and letting you become
the scapegoat for it.

875
01:06:23,396 --> 01:06:24,397
All of it.

876
01:06:27,066 --> 01:06:28,067
So?

877
01:06:29,569 --> 01:06:30,570
Tell me what you desire.

878
01:06:35,909 --> 01:06:36,910
If I tell you,

879
01:06:38,745 --> 01:06:39,746
can you give it to me?

880
01:06:41,331 --> 01:06:42,332
Seong Huiju.

881
01:06:42,415 --> 01:06:44,167
What I desire

882
01:06:45,335 --> 01:06:47,337
may be terribly difficult to attain.

883
01:06:52,759 --> 01:06:54,010
Let me get this straight.

884
01:06:54,093 --> 01:06:58,014
That woman and His Royal Highness
are actually an item?

885
01:06:58,097 --> 01:07:01,643
Didn't they seem like they had
nothing going on last time she visited?

886
01:07:01,726 --> 01:07:04,062
A secret rendezvous at a hotel?
That's a done deal.

887
01:07:04,145 --> 01:07:05,980
Still, don't you think it's a bit weird?

888
01:07:06,064 --> 01:07:07,941
His Royal Highness is so busy.

889
01:07:08,024 --> 01:07:09,817
When did he have time to date?

890
01:07:09,901 --> 01:07:10,944
Areum.

891
01:07:11,569 --> 01:07:13,196
I've told you a hundred times.

892
01:07:13,905 --> 01:07:16,449
When people say they can't date
because they're too busy,

893
01:07:17,283 --> 01:07:18,952
it's just an excuse.

894
01:07:32,840 --> 01:07:33,841
Do you remember?

895
01:07:36,010 --> 01:07:37,262
It's a Flower of Honor.

896
01:07:37,845 --> 01:07:39,514
The one I received after I beat you.

897
01:07:57,782 --> 01:07:59,033
Seven points!

898
01:08:13,715 --> 01:08:15,383
109 POINTS

899
01:08:28,146 --> 01:08:29,397
Didn't feel like crap?

900
01:08:32,442 --> 01:08:34,110
It felt like crap to me.

901
01:08:36,070 --> 01:08:38,197
Losing to someone

902
01:08:39,407 --> 01:08:40,450
who I could have beaten.

903
01:08:46,581 --> 01:08:48,291
My brother is an idiot.

904
01:08:49,375 --> 01:08:52,295
He got kicked out of the school
we made a donation to.

905
01:08:52,378 --> 01:08:55,548
He even managed to tank a business
that would've run on its own.

906
01:08:58,551 --> 01:09:00,345
But my father and the board

907
01:09:01,262 --> 01:09:03,973
are always dying to replace me with him

908
01:09:04,599 --> 01:09:07,018
whenever I make the slightest mistake.

909
01:09:08,269 --> 01:09:09,937
As if they've been biding their time.

910
01:09:11,189 --> 01:09:12,565
Why do you think that is?

911
01:09:14,067 --> 01:09:15,735
Because he was born before me?

912
01:09:15,818 --> 01:09:18,071
Because he's a son? And a legitimate heir?

913
01:09:21,032 --> 01:09:22,033
Oh…

914
01:09:23,409 --> 01:09:25,536
Perhaps it's because he married
into a noble family.

915
01:09:27,622 --> 01:09:28,873
That's why…

916
01:09:32,627 --> 01:09:34,420
I'm looking to marry up.

917
01:09:38,758 --> 01:09:40,551
You would marry me for nothing more

918
01:09:41,719 --> 01:09:42,929
than a hollow title?

919
01:09:43,012 --> 01:09:46,933
Because I've lost countless opportunities
simply for not having that title.

920
01:10:01,989 --> 01:10:04,909
Prepare yourself to become
the Grand Prince's wife.

921
01:10:13,209 --> 01:10:14,293
You will be up against…

922
01:10:17,797 --> 01:10:19,716
…the whole nation.

923
01:10:40,236 --> 01:10:43,156
PERFECT CROWN

924
01:11:19,275 --> 01:11:22,987
Your Royal Highness,
is your scandal with CEO Seong Huiju true?

925
01:11:23,070 --> 01:11:26,282
The top five trending key words
are all about you.

926
01:11:26,365 --> 01:11:27,825
He's even a good actor.

927
01:11:27,909 --> 01:11:29,744
You're really going to marry him?

928
01:11:29,827 --> 01:11:31,996
I have to marry him right now.

929
01:11:32,079 --> 01:11:34,081
Stay away
from His Royal Highness!

930
01:11:34,165 --> 01:11:36,125
She will be staying here
for the time being.

931
01:11:36,209 --> 01:11:38,169
An investigation is required.

932
01:11:38,252 --> 01:11:41,047
Cooperate with the Junghwajeon
Hall fire investigation, please.

933
01:11:41,130 --> 01:11:42,507
It's fine.

934
01:11:42,590 --> 01:11:45,092
I'm used to going up
against people like that.

935
01:11:45,176 --> 01:11:47,512
I must appear
insanely infatuated with you

936
01:11:48,805 --> 01:11:50,223
for people to believe

937
01:11:51,349 --> 01:11:53,184
this absurd marriage is genuine.

938
01:12:07,448 --> 01:12:09,075
PERFECT CROWN

939
01:12:09,158 --> 01:12:11,160
Translated by Justin S. Kim
